Recently I decided that I want to use oil pastels because it looked really vivid and reflected some quality.

Little did I know that the quality I thought was produced by the oil pastels was actually existed because of the taleted artists that used them.

And I am not even a little bit close to those artists both talent wise and experience wise.

Yes, I love trying new paint types, I love trying new mediums, new hobbies but my lack of consistency and the briefness of my enthusiasm is not taking me that further in my art journey.

Don't get me wrong I am glad that I try, and than I fail. But it doesn't even mather because the realization of creating something, that you are holding something that exists just because of you, can not be compared to many things.

I mean I guess after you have kids you can also hold them in your arms and look at it but than it starts to cry and now you are not even sure how you ended up like this. (I love kids) 

Anyways, long story short, if you are new to art stuff and you don't like messy art styles, oil pastels may not be really your thing. Who cares. 

Just do as you wish.

Order that 20 euros worth of yarn set you add to your basket once every month and try it. 

Who knows maybe this time it will be your thing ;)
